-- Cosan Plans to Boost Capacity to 110 Million Tons, Valor Economico Reports
-- B y   L u c i a   K a s s a i
-- 2010-09-23T11:35:52Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-09-23/cosan-plans-to-boost-capacity-to-110-million-tons-valor-economico-reports.html
Cosan SA Industria & Comercio  plans
to expand sugar-cane proccessing capacity to between 100 million
metric tons and 110 million tons in the next few years,  Valor
Economico  reported, citing Chairman and founder  Rubens Ometto .  The company currently crushes 63 million tons, according to
the newspaper. Cosan may expand existing plants and acquire or
build new ones, Ometto told the Sao Paulo-based newspaper.  To contact the reporter on this story:
 Lucia Kassai  in Sao Paulo at 
 lkassai@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Dale Crofts at   dcrofts@bloomberg.net . 